07:03.827 --> 07:21.988
 ♪  ♪

07:25.539 --> 07:27.298
[]Kate: William R. Alger
once said,

07:27.800 --> 07:31.478
"Men often make up in wrath
what they want in reason."

07:31.480 --> 07:33.814
This creep definitely
has a type.

07:33.816 --> 07:36.149
Both women were roughly
the same age, same look.

07:36.151 --> 07:38.069
Cute brunettes
are his thing.

07:38.071 --> 07:40.022
Myia Collins was single.
She grew up in the area

07:40.024 --> 07:42.646
and worked at the local
elementary school as a substitute teacher.

07:42.648 --> 07:44.566
Lauren White recently
moved back to Diamond Bar

07:44.568 --> 07:46.197
after she and her
husband split.

07:46.199 --> 07:49.174
It says here Lauren recently
started working part-time as a nurse.

07:49.176 --> 07:51.542
So both women had jobs
in which it wouldn't necessarily be noticed

07:51.544 --> 07:52.854
if they were gone for
a few days.

07:52.856 --> 07:54.230
What about friends
and family?

07:54.232 --> 07:55.894
Lauren has a sister,
Heather.

07:55.896 --> 07:58.581
Myia, not so much.
All her family is in Ohio.

07:58.583 --> 08:00.565
We know this guy's good
at being invisible.

08:00.567 --> 08:03.637
Both women were last seen leaving work
and never made it back home.

08:03.639 --> 08:05.365
He has to be abducting them
in public.

08:05.367 --> 08:06.645
Both were technically
single.

08:06.648 --> 08:08.214
They could have been
looking to meet new people.

08:08.216 --> 08:09.590
Maybe that was his in.

08:09.592 --> 08:11.862
Raymond Fernandez used to place
personal ads in the newspaper.

08:11.864 --> 08:13.622
He would seduce and rob
the women who answered them.

08:13.624 --> 08:15.350
The unsub could be
a lonely hearts killer.

08:15.352 --> 08:17.558
Maybe he hunts his victims at places
where singles hang out.

08:17.560 --> 08:20.086
You know, bars, night clubs,
chess tournaments.

08:22.551 --> 08:24.790
If the women turned
down his advances,

08:24.792 --> 08:26.294
it could have
emasculated him.

08:26.296 --> 08:29.494
You rejected me. I'm literally going to
make you feel my pain.

08:29.496 --> 08:30.742
But he's not breaking
their hearts,

08:30.744 --> 08:31.926
he's breaking their bodies.

08:31.927 --> 08:34.101
All right, when we land, JJ, you
and Kate go to the M.E.

08:34.102 --> 08:35.669
Morgan, reach out
to the families.

08:35.671 --> 08:37.684
The rest of us will
set up at the precinct.

08:41.335 --> 08:42.933
Agent Hotchner,
thanks for coming out.

08:42.936 --> 08:45.046
Detective Davenport.
This is Agent Rossi, Dr. Reid.

08:45.048 --> 08:47.126
Welcome.
Right this way.

08:47.128 --> 08:48.501
Thank you.

08:48.503 --> 08:51.125
To be honest, this kind of thing
doesn't happen around here.

08:51.127 --> 08:53.238
This guy has
the entire city on edge.

08:53.240 --> 08:54.838
A serial killer
will do that.

08:54.839 --> 08:57.525
Your team can set up in here.
Thank you.

09:01.880 --> 09:03.926
Have any witnesses
come forward?

09:03.927 --> 09:05.877
I have my guys out
interviewing local merchants,

09:05.879 --> 09:07.478
but so far we're
coming up empty.

09:07.480 --> 09:09.078
Have you noticed any variations
in traffic patterns

09:09.079 --> 09:10.581
near where the bodies
were found?

09:10.583 --> 09:12.405
That road's a commuter
nightmare. Why?

09:12.407 --> 09:14.997
The unsub had to know
the traffic in order to escape detection.

09:14.999 --> 09:16.437
Grand Avenue's
18 miles long

09:16.439 --> 09:18.069
and runs through
4 other cities.

09:18.071 --> 09:20.630
He could have spread out
the dump sites but chose not to.

09:20.632 --> 09:22.550
Both victims were found
within a mile of one another.

09:22.552 --> 09:25.141
That's a huge risk
the unsub didn't have to take.

09:25.143 --> 09:26.709
The area must be
important to him.

09:26.711 --> 09:28.597
Or convenient.
What are you willing to bet

09:28.600 --> 09:30.966
the unsub either lives
or works nearby?

09:30.967 --> 09:33.045
The tox screens came back
negative,

09:33.048 --> 09:36.245
however, C.O.D. on both wasn't
the lacerations to their necks

09:36.247 --> 09:37.525
like I initially thought.

09:37.527 --> 09:38.710
So what was it?

09:38.712 --> 09:40.790
Blunt force trauma
to the back of the head.

09:40.792 --> 09:43.350
In fact, the lacerations
were done postmortem.

09:43.352 --> 09:45.142
The slicing of throats
is a symbolic way

09:45.143 --> 09:46.421
of silencing his victims.

09:46.423 --> 09:49.269
Maybe he feels he doesn't have
a voice himself.

09:49.272 --> 09:51.126
Looks like he might
have hesitated.

09:51.127 --> 09:53.365
Yeah. But the incision
across Lauren's throat

09:53.368 --> 09:54.934
was much more precise.

09:54.936 --> 09:56.598
His confidence
in the way he kills

09:56.600 --> 09:58.102
could be building
with each victim.

09:58.104 --> 10:01.046
With Myia he literally
beat her with his bare hands.

10:01.048 --> 10:02.710
You can tell
from the bruising here.

10:02.712 --> 10:05.301
She suffered multiple fractures
in her arms and torso.

10:05.303 --> 10:07.414
Lauren had the same type
of bruising,

10:07.416 --> 10:09.653
but her injuries
were much more brutal.

10:09.655 --> 10:11.254
He introduced
a blunt object.

10:11.256 --> 10:13.302
Brutality could be
important to his fantasy.

10:13.303 --> 10:15.477
Maybe he's trying to perfect
his method of torture.

10:15.479 --> 10:16.406
Or he's devolving.

10:16.408 --> 10:17.685
Maybe the torture
isn't enough.

10:17.687 --> 10:20.598
There could be something
else he wants from his victims.

10:22.712 --> 10:24.822
Your sister moved
back here 3 months ago.

10:24.823 --> 10:26.965
Was that to be closer
to you?

10:26.968 --> 10:29.813
We had a falling out
about a year ago.

10:29.815 --> 10:31.766
It had only been in
the last couple of months

10:31.768 --> 10:33.526
we started patching things up.

10:33.528 --> 10:34.646
If you don't mind
me asking,

10:34.648 --> 10:36.662
what caused the rift
in your relationship?

10:36.664 --> 10:40.598
When our folks split,
she took it the hardest.

10:40.600 --> 10:43.286
She felt like
our dad just left.

10:43.288 --> 10:45.462
She turned to partying.

10:45.464 --> 10:48.501
There were times I would go days
without hearing from her.

10:48.503 --> 10:51.574
Lauren recently
filed for divorce.

10:51.576 --> 10:53.174
Can you tell me
about her husband?

10:53.175 --> 10:55.254
I never even met him.

10:55.256 --> 10:57.590
They hooked up
at some bar.

10:57.592 --> 10:58.902
She'd only known him
like a week

10:58.904 --> 11:01.558
before I got a text saying they
had gotten married in Vegas.

11:01.559 --> 11:04.725
And when things didn't work out for
the two of them, she came back here.

11:04.727 --> 11:06.582
Did the divorce change her?

11:07.607 --> 11:09.814
She was the same Lauren.

11:09.816 --> 11:13.302
Still looking for a man
to validate her.

11:13.304 --> 11:14.485
Thanks, Garcia.

11:14.487 --> 11:16.565
Well, Lauren's ex-husband
Doug checked out.

11:16.567 --> 11:19.637
He's been in Seattle touring with
his band the past few weeks.

11:19.639 --> 11:21.813
According to her sister,
she was promiscuous.

11:21.815 --> 11:24.054
Said she would fall
head over heels for any man

11:24.056 --> 11:25.782
who showed her the slightest
amount of attention.

11:25.784 --> 11:27.477
That may rule out
the lonely hearts theory.

11:27.479 --> 11:29.493
That type of unsub typically
thrives off of challenge.

11:29.495 --> 11:31.221
Lauren wouldn't have
given him that.

11:31.223 --> 11:34.197
You know what? There might be another
connection we haven't considered.

11:34.199 --> 11:36.981
Myia was never promoted to full-time
because supervisors described her

11:36.983 --> 11:38.517
as quiet and submissive.

11:38.519 --> 11:41.750
Heather said Lauren struggled with
needing a man to validate her worth.

11:41.752 --> 11:43.254
It speaks to both
their levels of confidence.

11:43.256 --> 11:47.830
This unsub could be targeting
women with self-image issues.

11:48.983 --> 11:51.094
[Baby crying]

11:54.967 --> 11:57.206
[Door opens]

11:57.208 --> 11:58.966
Greta Thomas?

11:58.967 --> 12:00.694
Yes, that's me.

12:02.231 --> 12:05.142
Honey, I need you
to stay here.

12:05.144 --> 12:07.254
Mommy
will be right back.

12:12.664 --> 12:14.165
My name is Peter.

12:14.167 --> 12:15.957
I'm going to be
your caseworker.

12:15.959 --> 12:17.589
Right this way.

12:19.288 --> 12:21.302
Have a seat.

12:24.792 --> 12:26.358
Can I get you
something to drink?

12:26.360 --> 12:28.278
No, thank you.

12:29.496 --> 12:33.206
I just need to verify
a few things before we get started.

12:38.423 --> 12:40.565
There you go.

12:40.567 --> 12:43.317
Thank you.

12:43.319 --> 12:45.973
Is this the first time
you've been here?

12:47.287 --> 12:50.550
My son saw it happen
this time.

12:53.944 --> 12:57.526
I never wanted him
to see me like this.

12:57.527 --> 12:59.413
How old is he?

12:59.415 --> 13:02.357
7. [Crying]

13:16.215 --> 13:19.285
You two have the option
of staying here,

13:19.287 --> 13:23.221
or if you have someplace else you'd
rather stay the night...

13:23.223 --> 13:26.773
Uh, I have a friend
we could stay with.

13:26.775 --> 13:28.469
Good.

13:28.471 --> 13:31.382
Now, I need you
to tell me

13:31.383 --> 13:35.061
exactly what your
husband did to you.

13:36.023 --> 13:37.493
Why target women
with low self-esteem?

13:37.495 --> 13:38.901
What does it get him?

13:38.903 --> 13:40.853
Well, it makes him
easier to control.

13:40.855 --> 13:42.741
He prolongs the torture
because the more he does,

13:42.743 --> 13:44.405
the more powerful
he feels.

13:44.407 --> 13:48.181
Which could mean he doesn't
feel very important in his everyday life.

13:51.031 --> 13:54.421
Kate: Maybe he has low self-worth.
Like attracts like.

13:54.423 --> 13:56.373
Hotch: And his only chance
of dominance

13:56.375 --> 13:57.909
is to target
other submissives.

13:57.911 --> 13:59.413
If this is about
power and control,

13:59.415 --> 14:01.781
maybe the stressor occurred when
the unsub didn't have any?

14:01.783 --> 14:04.022
Ok.

14:04.023 --> 14:06.454
Thank you.

14:13.463 --> 14:15.445
These women could be
surrogates for the person

14:15.448 --> 14:17.173
he holds responsible
for his pain.

14:17.175 --> 14:19.349
Something could have
happened to him when he was a child.

14:19.351 --> 14:21.462
If he felt powerless
in is childhood,

14:21.464 --> 14:24.630
then having a taste of power now
would be like a drug.

14:24.631 --> 14:25.781
Exactly.

14:25.783 --> 14:27.701
And he'll be looking
for his next fix.

14:27.703 --> 14:30.197
I appreciate you letting us
spend the night.

14:30.199 --> 14:34.100
I couldn't bring myself to let Conner
sleep at that place.

14:34.103 --> 14:37.974
No, I'm fine. I just--
I just need to get out of here.

14:37.975 --> 14:40.406
He could come back
at any minute.

14:40.407 --> 14:43.477
Text you when
we're on our way.

15:01.432 --> 15:02.742
Conner?

15:02.744 --> 15:06.293
Did you pack
your toothbrush?

15:09.175 --> 15:10.965
Conner!

15:16.503 --> 15:21.334
[Cartoon music on TV]

15:22.583 --> 15:24.885
Conner?

15:28.119 --> 15:31.573
Didn't you hear me
calling you?

15:31.575 --> 15:33.813
And how many times
have I told you

15:33.815 --> 15:36.501
not to go to the cabinet
and get candy?

15:36.503 --> 15:39.285
I didn't, Mom.
The man gave it to me.

15:41.207 --> 15:42.485
What man?

15:42.487 --> 15:44.277
That one.

15:55.560 --> 15:57.478
[]Her name is Greta Thomas.

15:57.480 --> 15:59.430
According to the neighbor,
her son Conner

15:59.432 --> 16:01.254
knocked on their door
saying a man took his mom.

16:01.256 --> 16:02.790
She looks like
the other two victims.

16:02.792 --> 16:04.069
Any word on her husband?

16:04.071 --> 16:05.638
Garcia's trying
to locate him.

16:05.640 --> 16:07.526
Apparently he travels
a lot for work.

16:07.528 --> 16:08.774
Did Conner see anything?

16:08.776 --> 16:10.246
He was able to give
a description,

16:10.248 --> 16:11.430
but not much to go on.

16:11.432 --> 16:13.222
Well, we might get more
if we gave him a cognitive,

16:13.224 --> 16:15.015
but we're gonna need to wait and
get a guardian's permission first.

16:15.016 --> 16:16.678
This is the first time that the unsub
broke into someone's house

16:16.680 --> 16:19.621
and left a witness. Usually he just
does it out in the open.

16:19.623 --> 16:21.382
Maybe he's getting closer
to his ideal surrogate.

16:21.384 --> 16:24.166
If that's the case, what makes
Greta different from the others?

16:24.168 --> 16:25.093
She's a mother.

16:25.096 --> 16:27.813
[Cell phone rings]

16:27.815 --> 16:29.349
Tell me you found
the husband.

16:29.352 --> 16:32.518
Affirmative, sir, but you're never
gonna believe where.

16:33.544 --> 16:35.110
We believe we're looking
for a white male

16:35.112 --> 16:37.254
in his mid- to late 30s
who has a history

16:37.256 --> 16:39.014
of physical
and psychological abuse.

16:39.016 --> 16:40.997
This unsub is
a projecting punisher,

16:40.999 --> 16:43.046
which means he's victimizing
women he believes

16:43.048 --> 16:47.078
in one way or another
haven't stood up for themselves.

16:50.951 --> 16:53.189
With the first two victims,
he caused injuries

16:53.192 --> 16:54.566
that are consistent
with domestic abuse.

16:54.568 --> 16:56.614
With his latest victim,
Greta Thomas,

16:56.615 --> 16:59.109
not only is she a mother,
but she's an actual victim of abuse.

16:59.112 --> 17:00.710
At her husband
was jailed last night

17:00.711 --> 17:02.246
after an altercation
at the family home.

17:02.248 --> 17:04.069
Which is why we believe
the unsub's mother

17:04.071 --> 17:05.925
was the one that actually
suffered physical abuse.

17:05.928 --> 17:07.846
It's likely he blamed her
for allowing the violence

17:07.848 --> 17:09.030
to enter and continue
in the home.

17:09.031 --> 17:11.205
Rather than viewing
his mother as a victim,

17:11.208 --> 17:12.646
he holds resentment
towards her

17:12.647 --> 17:15.013
because of the upheaval
and fear he lived with.

17:18.760 --> 17:20.806
[Crash]
Man: You're pathetic!

17:20.808 --> 17:23.301
I want some respect
around this house!

17:23.304 --> 17:25.637
This house is a mess!
You're a mess!

17:25.640 --> 17:27.205
Rossi: This man doesn't
hate is mother.

17:27.208 --> 17:29.830
He hates the idea
of that she represented.

17:29.832 --> 17:31.078
Hesitation marks
on the earlier victims

17:31.079 --> 17:33.445
indicate that the unsub
feels conflicted by his actions.

17:33.447 --> 17:35.814
It's possible he does not want to hurt
the women he abducts,

17:35.816 --> 17:37.541
but somehow
he feels he has to.

17:37.543 --> 17:39.430
Given his warped
sense of justice,

17:39.432 --> 17:41.350
he may see himself as
a protector of these women.

17:41.352 --> 17:43.174
He may even want them
to fight back.

17:43.176 --> 17:44.806
He lost control
at an early age,

17:44.808 --> 17:46.758
and he's desperate
to regain it.

17:46.760 --> 17:49.926
We should look at domestic abuse
cases going back 25 to 30 years.

17:49.927 --> 17:51.526
JJ: Take a look at locations
battered women frequent--

17:51.528 --> 17:53.701
group homes, women's
shelters, legal hearings.

17:53.703 --> 17:57.093
For now our primary goal is to bring
Greta Thomas home alive and safe.

17:57.095 --> 17:59.078
Thank you.

18:09.288 --> 18:14.469
[Muffled cries]

18:19.623 --> 18:21.701
You were supposed
to help us.

18:21.703 --> 18:24.518
I told you everything
he did to me.

18:24.520 --> 18:26.757
Oh, my God!

18:26.759 --> 18:29.733
Where's Conner?
What did you do to him?!

18:29.735 --> 18:33.893
He's fine, now that he's no longer
in that toxic environment.

18:33.896 --> 18:36.518
What are you talking about?

18:36.520 --> 18:40.806
You think this was the first time
he saw that monster hit you?

18:42.375 --> 18:46.726
The screaming, the fighting,
the arguments.

18:46.728 --> 18:49.382
You think he's stupid?

18:52.775 --> 18:56.486
I can't imagine what
that must do to a child.

18:56.488 --> 18:58.693
But I made a mistake.

18:58.695 --> 19:03.045
Which you let it happen
over and over again.

19:04.776 --> 19:08.806
Which is partly why
I think you're perfect.

19:10.759 --> 19:14.149
Rossi: Final M.E. report
just came through.

19:14.151 --> 19:17.510
Take a look at
the stomach contents.

19:17.512 --> 19:20.390
Saltwater, honey,
ginger, and tea.

19:20.392 --> 19:23.302
She also found multiple ulcerations
of the vocal chords of both victims,

19:23.303 --> 19:25.573
most likely
from all the screaming.

19:26.920 --> 19:29.382
Spill it, kid. I can see
you got a theory.

19:29.384 --> 19:31.686
The saltwater could serve
another purpose.

19:31.687 --> 19:35.013
Honey, ginger tea, and saltwater
are often used to treat sore throats.

19:35.015 --> 19:37.509
Maybe something about
their voices is what's driving him.

19:37.512 --> 19:40.262
But a sadist wouldn't
go to such lengths to heal his victims.

19:40.263 --> 19:43.334
Especially when his final act of rage
is slicing their throats.

19:43.336 --> 19:45.510
This guy's destroying the very thing
he's trying to preserve.

19:45.512 --> 19:48.134
All the torture could simply
be a means to an end.

19:48.136 --> 19:51.142
If it's not about the
violence, what's it about?

19:51.143 --> 19:53.765
Their screams.

19:55.016 --> 19:56.901
[Coughing] Please!

19:56.903 --> 19:58.021
We can't stop.

19:58.024 --> 20:01.286
Not until you give me
what I want.

20:10.631 --> 20:15.141
♪ I've got a great big
bundle of love ♪

20:15.143 --> 20:16.326
♪ and I have... ♪

20:16.328 --> 20:19.110
How the hell do you think that
makes me feel, huh?

20:19.112 --> 20:21.318
I said I'm sorry.

20:21.320 --> 20:23.302
I bust my butt
at work all day,

20:23.304 --> 20:25.414
and all I ask
is for a hot meal.

20:25.416 --> 20:27.461
Honey, I'm sorry.

20:27.463 --> 20:30.181
Please, I know
this is all my fault.

20:30.183 --> 20:31.749
You think I want
to do this?

20:31.751 --> 20:34.822
Look, I know
you had a rough day.

20:34.824 --> 20:36.774
So why do you
have to make it worse?

20:36.775 --> 20:38.629
I'll do better.
I promise.

20:38.631 --> 20:41.382
I'm tired of giving you
second chances.

20:41.384 --> 20:42.950
You're on speaker,
Garcia.

20:42.952 --> 20:45.254
You guys, I have searched every
shelter up and down the West Coast.

20:45.255 --> 20:47.141
I can't find Greta's name
anywhere.

20:47.144 --> 20:49.189
Could she have
registered anonymously?

20:49.191 --> 20:51.269
Records are kept confidential,
but trust me,

20:51.271 --> 20:53.158
if she was listed
in any of them,

20:53.160 --> 20:54.918
your nearsighted wonder girl
would have found her.

20:54.920 --> 20:57.158
Maybe that's the answer
to where this guy finds his victims.

20:57.160 --> 20:58.629
What if he works
in the system?

20:58.631 --> 21:01.094
Women go to him for help
and end up as victims.

21:01.096 --> 21:02.277
Hey, Garcia--

21:02.279 --> 21:03.622
Already on it.
Give me a minute.

21:03.624 --> 21:05.062
If I find anything,
I'll hit you right back.

21:05.063 --> 21:07.653
All right, so the physical
abuse he witnessed in the household

21:07.656 --> 21:09.510
imprinted on him.
That's why he's conflicted.

21:09.511 --> 21:11.845
He sees himself
as protector and abuser.

21:11.848 --> 21:14.501
And now he's taking on
the role of the abuser

21:14.503 --> 21:16.133
re-enacting what
happened to his mother.

21:16.135 --> 21:17.926
Typically, unsubs with
this type of nostalgia

21:17.928 --> 21:19.397
keep some kind of a trophy.

21:19.399 --> 21:20.965
We haven't seen any evidence
of that here.

21:20.967 --> 21:24.421
We've profiled that what he wants
most from them are their screams.

21:24.423 --> 21:26.981
Ok, but how is
a scream a trophy?

21:26.983 --> 21:30.694
It's not.
Unless he's recording them.

22:38.312 --> 22:40.486
Greta: I know
this is all my fault.

22:40.488 --> 22:42.725
Unsub: You think
I want to do this?

22:42.727 --> 22:45.638
Look, I know you had
a rough night.

22:45.640 --> 22:47.302
Why did you have to
make it worse?

22:47.304 --> 22:49.574
I'll do better.
I promise.

22:49.576 --> 22:52.934
I'm tired of giving you
second chances.

22:55.009 --> 22:56.255
[]Hey, talk to us,
hot stuff.

22:56.257 --> 22:57.696
I feel like I don't
deserve to talk to you,

22:57.697 --> 23:00.096
because I have terrible news.
I'm hitting the hardest wall

23:00.097 --> 23:01.726
in domestic abuse cases
of yesteryear.

23:01.728 --> 23:02.975
To say there are a plethora

23:02.977 --> 23:04.767
is a severe injustice
to the word plethora.

23:04.768 --> 23:06.463
I can't narrow it down alone.
I need help.

23:06.465 --> 23:08.415
Based on the current victim pool,
the mother would have been

23:08.417 --> 23:10.623
In her 20s back then.
Thank you, thank you.

23:10.624 --> 23:11.678
Keep talking.

23:11.680 --> 23:13.759
The unsub most likely
grew up nearby, Garcia.

23:13.760 --> 23:16.190
Check recurring abuse cases
within the comfort zone.

23:16.193 --> 23:18.687
Look for women who made
frequent trips to the E.R.

23:18.689 --> 23:21.215
But not for abuse.
More like a freak accident,

23:21.217 --> 23:24.062
like falling down the stairs
or extensive clumsiness.

23:24.064 --> 23:25.726
Uh-huh. Now we're
getting somewhere.

23:25.728 --> 23:27.262
And the occupation
might match as well,

23:27.265 --> 23:28.735
so look for teachers
or nurses.

23:28.737 --> 23:30.622
Hello, promising candidate.
Karen Holden,

23:30.624 --> 23:32.094
third-grade
teacher at the time.

23:32.096 --> 23:34.270
She went to the E.R.
multiple times,

23:34.272 --> 23:37.150
courtesy of her icky,
icky abusive husband Frank Holden.

23:37.152 --> 23:38.782
Where's Frank
and Karen now?

23:38.785 --> 23:42.207
Dead. Like in a tragic story
of Shakespearean proportions

23:42.208 --> 23:45.022
kind of way. They died in
a murder-suicide 25 years ago.

23:45.024 --> 23:45.950
What happened?

23:45.953 --> 23:47.263
Uh, Frank had
a drinking problem.

23:47.265 --> 23:49.471
He got punchy with Karen,
like literally,

23:49.472 --> 23:51.486
an argument ensued and ended up
with Karen having her throat slashed

23:51.488 --> 23:52.991
and Frank with a bullet
in his head.

23:52.993 --> 23:55.039
I am guessing
they had a child?

23:55.040 --> 23:56.255
They did, indeed.

23:56.256 --> 23:58.686
Little Peter Holden.
He was 7 at the time.

23:58.689 --> 23:59.743
He saw the whole thing.

23:59.744 --> 24:01.086
Do we know where
Peter is now?

24:01.088 --> 24:02.591
Negatory. After his parents
died, he was put

24:02.593 --> 24:04.574
in the foster care system
until he was 18,

24:04.576 --> 24:05.855
and that's where
the paper trail ends.

24:05.856 --> 24:08.574
Diamond Bar's a small town.
Probably changed his name

24:08.576 --> 24:10.783
to escape the notoriety
of his parents' deaths.

24:10.785 --> 24:13.374
I'll check court records
and see if I can find a breadcrumb.

24:13.376 --> 24:15.071
All right, thanks,
baby girl.

24:15.073 --> 24:16.927
Wait, wait, there's a name that keeps
coming up in the old hospital records.

24:16.929 --> 24:19.007
John Folkmore.
He was an officer who responded

24:19.009 --> 24:21.119
to a majority of the calls
from the Holden residence.

24:21.121 --> 24:23.711
Johnny. He retired a few years back,
but he still lives in town.

24:23.713 --> 24:25.950
You think he might know
what happened to the kid?

24:25.952 --> 24:27.999
It'd be good
to talk to him.

24:28.928 --> 24:30.687
[Door slams]

24:32.289 --> 24:34.815
You didn't do it right.

24:34.817 --> 24:36.703
I shouldn't have to do this.

24:36.705 --> 24:38.239
What are you talking about?

24:38.240 --> 24:39.646
You know what
I'm talking about.

24:39.648 --> 24:41.087
I don't.
Just let me go.

24:41.089 --> 24:42.431
I promise I won't
tell any--

24:42.432 --> 24:43.710
Why are you holding back?

24:43.713 --> 24:44.703
I did what you wanted.

24:44.704 --> 24:45.630
No, you didn't!

24:45.633 --> 24:47.007
[Sobbing]

24:54.721 --> 24:56.383
[Grunting]

25:03.136 --> 25:05.887
Do you think I want
to do this?

25:05.889 --> 25:08.702
Then don't.

25:08.704 --> 25:11.198
Please, just let me go.

25:14.912 --> 25:16.159
I can't.

25:17.184 --> 25:19.614
Why won't you do what I ask?!

25:19.616 --> 25:21.150
I have.

25:21.153 --> 25:24.831
No! It's not right!

25:24.832 --> 25:27.806
It's not the way it was!

25:27.808 --> 25:28.926
Do it the way I said!

25:28.928 --> 25:32.446
It has to happen the way
I explained it to you!

25:32.448 --> 25:35.134
Do it the right way!

25:35.136 --> 25:37.311
Do it!

25:37.312 --> 25:40.766
Do you remember
that little guy?

25:42.529 --> 25:44.735
Peter Holden.

25:44.736 --> 25:47.135
Never forgot that face.

25:47.137 --> 25:49.343
Back in the day
you responded to a number

25:49.345 --> 25:51.711
of domestic abuse calls
at the Holden residence.

25:51.712 --> 25:54.366
At least once a week.

25:54.368 --> 25:58.303
You knew how violent Frank Holden was
and you never arrested him.

25:58.305 --> 25:59.582
Why?

26:00.673 --> 26:03.422
Karen covered for him.

26:03.424 --> 26:07.518
She wrote the book
on excuses.

26:07.520 --> 26:09.982
If she wasn't telling me
she fell down stairs,

26:09.984 --> 26:12.703
she was bumping into
cabinets.

26:12.705 --> 26:14.111
You don't know
how many times

26:14.113 --> 26:16.414
I wanted her
to come forward.

26:18.528 --> 26:23.934
Part of me blames myself
for what happened that night.

26:23.936 --> 26:27.262
Will you tell me
about Peter?

26:28.928 --> 26:31.231
He was a good kid.

26:31.233 --> 26:34.303
He loved baseball.

26:34.304 --> 26:37.886
He didn't deserve to grow up
in a house like that.

26:39.264 --> 26:41.246
Kate: When was the last
time you saw him?

26:41.249 --> 26:43.134
A few nights before.

26:43.136 --> 26:46.782
I stopped by the house
to drop off a gift.

26:46.784 --> 26:49.471
I bought him
a cassette recorder.

26:51.872 --> 26:55.966
That's an odd gift
to give a 7-year-old, don't you think?

26:57.921 --> 27:00.510
It wasn't a gift, was it?

27:00.512 --> 27:03.679
You wanted him to capture
his mother's abuse.

27:05.441 --> 27:07.999
I--I don't know
what I was thinking.

27:08.000 --> 27:10.751
I was so frustrated
with that whole situation.

27:10.753 --> 27:12.959
I made a promise
to the kid,

27:12.960 --> 27:15.518
if he could get me
the recording...

27:15.520 --> 27:19.198
I could finally put
that son of a bitch in jail.

27:19.200 --> 27:24.606
You were the only positive
male role model he ever had.

27:25.920 --> 27:29.470
Someone had to be.

27:29.472 --> 27:32.094
[Indistinct chatter]

27:35.617 --> 27:38.175
I think Peter changed
his last name to Folkmore.

27:38.176 --> 27:39.326
The officer's last name?

27:39.328 --> 27:41.375
Yeah. Think about it.
Whenever Peter and his mother

27:41.377 --> 27:43.679
were in trouble,
who did they call?

27:43.680 --> 27:47.614
Folkmore. He became
a surrogate father.

28:10.432 --> 28:11.550
[Crash]

28:13.600 --> 28:15.326
Frank: You are pathetic!

28:15.329 --> 28:17.343
I cannot take this anymore!

28:17.345 --> 28:20.127
I am so sick of you!

28:20.129 --> 28:21.502
The house is a mess!

28:21.504 --> 28:22.751
You are a mess!

28:22.753 --> 28:23.711
[Dish smashes]

28:23.713 --> 28:24.703
When I come home,

28:24.704 --> 28:27.198
I want to be treated
with some respect.

28:27.201 --> 28:30.367
[Indistinct]

28:30.368 --> 28:34.494
I can't even stand
to look at your face anymore!

28:34.496 --> 28:36.990
How the hell do you think
it makes me feel, huh?

28:36.992 --> 28:38.174
I said I'm sorry.

28:38.176 --> 28:40.575
I bust my butt at work
all day

28:40.576 --> 28:43.038
and all I ask for
is a hot meal.

28:43.040 --> 28:45.214
Honey, I know
this is my fault.

28:45.216 --> 28:46.590
You think I want
to do this?

28:46.592 --> 28:47.518
[Record playing]

28:47.520 --> 28:49.054
I know you had
a rough day at work.

28:49.056 --> 28:51.326
So why do you
have to make it worse?

28:51.328 --> 28:52.415
I'll do better.
I promise.

28:52.417 --> 28:54.654
I am tired of giving you
second chances.

28:54.656 --> 28:57.438
Stop! Frank, please,
put the knife down.

28:57.440 --> 28:59.294
He can hear.
He's in the other room.

28:59.296 --> 29:01.599
Stop! No, Frank--

29:01.600 --> 29:05.822
♪ you have the whole world
wrapped up in your hand ♪

29:05.824 --> 29:07.198
Mommy!

29:07.200 --> 29:10.494
♪ One little hand ♪

29:10.496 --> 29:11.902
Mom?
♪ my great big ♪

29:11.904 --> 29:13.566
♪ bundle of love ♪

29:13.568 --> 29:18.079
♪ and you're gonna see ♪

29:25.344 --> 29:27.070
Dad?

29:27.073 --> 29:28.543
No!

29:28.545 --> 29:29.855
[Gunshot]

29:29.857 --> 29:32.255
[Record scratches, repeats]
♪ little man--little man--

29:32.256 --> 29:34.910
little man... ♪

29:34.912 --> 29:37.950
According to child services,
Peter was in and out of foster homes.

29:37.952 --> 29:40.351
Says he carried a tape recorder
with him wherever he went.

29:40.352 --> 29:42.462
In his statement of the night
when his parents died,

29:42.464 --> 29:43.870
he said they were arguing.
Maybe he recorded it.

29:43.872 --> 29:45.630
John never mentioned
Peter giving him a tape.

29:45.632 --> 29:48.639
Maybe Folkmore didn't know. Karen died
before Peter cold give him the tape.

29:48.640 --> 29:50.622
You think he would hold on
to it for all those years?

29:50.625 --> 29:52.031
Well, it's possible.
The tape would have been

29:52.032 --> 29:53.566
his last memory of his mother,
so he kept it for himself.

29:53.568 --> 29:55.134
Something must have
happened to the original recording.

29:55.136 --> 29:56.479
[Cell phone rings]
There's our trigger.

29:56.481 --> 29:59.199
He's not going to stop
until he replaces what he lost.

29:59.200 --> 30:00.446
Hey, sweetness,
give it to me good.

30:00.448 --> 30:04.063
I will. Peter Folkmore
has only existed in the system

30:04.065 --> 30:05.151
for the last 16 years.

30:05.152 --> 30:07.646
He works at the Angel
Network for Women

30:07.649 --> 30:08.799
for the last 8 years.

30:08.800 --> 30:10.302
Working there allowed him to do
for other women

30:10.304 --> 30:11.743
what he couldn't do
for his mother.

30:11.745 --> 30:13.310
Karen wasn't the only one
making distress calls.

30:13.312 --> 30:15.390
A month ago, Peter called
the fire department

30:15.392 --> 30:16.895
regarding a small fire
in his basement.

30:16.897 --> 30:20.255
According to insurance claims,
he lost a slew of, quote,

30:20.256 --> 30:21.343
"priceless belongings."

30:21.345 --> 30:23.999
Reid: That's right before
the murders started.

30:28.288 --> 30:29.246
Kate: Do you have an address?

30:29.248 --> 30:30.238
Work and home
already sent to you.

30:30.240 --> 30:31.486
JJ and I
will take the house.

30:31.488 --> 30:33.342
We'll grab the others
and go to the shelter.

30:39.424 --> 30:40.734
Oh!

31:09.440 --> 31:11.998
Where are you, Greta?

31:13.888 --> 31:17.310
Come out, come out,
wherever you are.

31:26.048 --> 31:30.910
The sooner we get this right,
the sooner we can end this.

31:44.928 --> 31:47.679
♪ I've got a big,
big bundle of love ♪

31:47.680 --> 31:50.078
Getting warmer?

31:50.080 --> 31:54.334
♪ And I have saved it
all for you ♪

31:54.336 --> 31:58.590
[Song continues]

31:58.592 --> 32:02.974
♪ Honey, that your
lovin' is true ♪

32:02.976 --> 32:08.126
♪ you have the whole world
wrapped up in your hands... ♪

32:08.128 --> 32:11.198
[Screaming]

32:11.200 --> 32:12.158
No! No! No!

32:12.160 --> 32:13.822
Yeah, you. You.

32:13.824 --> 32:16.223
Uhh!

32:16.224 --> 32:18.270
Unh!

32:18.272 --> 32:20.254
♪ You don't know
how much I love you ♪

32:20.256 --> 32:21.470
I really wish
you hadn't done that.

32:21.472 --> 32:24.414
[Crying out]

32:28.050 --> 32:31.408
[][Sirens]

32:34.706 --> 32:36.528
You ruined it.
We were getting somewhere.

32:36.529 --> 32:39.920
We can try again.
Just please don't do this!

32:40.913 --> 32:42.511
No! Unh!

32:42.513 --> 32:43.823
[Tires screech]

32:43.825 --> 32:47.856
[Siren]

32:47.858 --> 32:50.319
Help! Help!

32:51.858 --> 32:53.616
Come on!

33:24.625 --> 33:27.535
Uhh!

33:46.641 --> 33:48.623
Scream for me.

33:49.713 --> 33:50.671
[Gunshot]

33:50.673 --> 33:53.551
[Bat clatters on floor]

33:55.089 --> 33:57.328
You wish.

34:01.905 --> 34:04.527
We need a medic
down here ASAP.

34:05.745 --> 34:07.151
Greta.

34:07.153 --> 34:09.263
Greta, are you ok?

34:09.264 --> 34:11.056
Conner?

34:11.056 --> 34:14.255
He's ok. He's safe.
He's safe. I promise.

34:14.257 --> 34:17.232
You're gonna be ok.
An ambulance is on the way.

34:18.257 --> 34:20.655
Peter: Scream for me.

34:20.657 --> 34:21.998
[Gunshot]

34:22.001 --> 34:24.047
[Bat clatters]

34:30.321 --> 34:33.614
Hotch: "Nothing can drive one
closer to his own insanity

34:33.618 --> 34:36.655
than a haunting memory
refusing its own death."

34:36.657 --> 34:39.120
Darnella Ford.

34:53.553 --> 34:54.703
How's the head?

34:54.705 --> 34:55.630
Oh, I'll survive.

34:55.632 --> 34:58.287
What about you?

34:58.289 --> 34:59.503
I know that look.

34:59.505 --> 35:02.799
Face of a worried mom.
What's going on?

35:02.801 --> 35:03.728
[Sighs]

35:03.730 --> 35:06.191
Meg is going on
her first date tonight.

35:06.193 --> 35:08.143
Really?

35:08.145 --> 35:09.488
At 13?

35:09.490 --> 35:11.248
It's not really--
it's not really a date.

35:11.249 --> 35:12.174
It's with boys.

35:12.177 --> 35:14.255
But when I was 13
and I went to the mall

35:14.257 --> 35:17.071
to meet boys,
it was a date.

35:17.073 --> 35:19.503
Yeah. Times
are a-changin', my friend.

35:19.505 --> 35:23.536
I just keep reminding myself,
it is just the mall.

35:23.538 --> 35:26.575
I don't think parents are ever ready
for their kids to grow up.

35:26.577 --> 35:29.455
It feels like yesterday
she was in diapers.

35:29.457 --> 35:32.528
Teenagers. I don't know how
my mom survived.

35:32.530 --> 35:34.223
Ooh. Mine either.

35:34.225 --> 35:37.647
Well, right now Henry still thinks
girls have cooties. So...

35:37.649 --> 35:41.551
He won't feel that way
a few years from now, so treasure it.

35:45.105 --> 35:47.887
Don't you wish
you could just...

35:47.890 --> 35:49.967
keep them innocent
forever?

35:49.969 --> 35:52.719
Yeah.

36:00.370 --> 36:02.992
Relax. We're early.

36:02.993 --> 36:05.871
As long as we make it back before
curfew, we're good.

36:05.873 --> 36:07.983
Otherwise there'll be
hell to pay for.

36:07.985 --> 36:10.191
What did you tell
your folks?

36:10.193 --> 36:11.663
The truth. Sort of.

36:11.665 --> 36:14.287
I told them we were
meeting two guys in our biology class.

36:14.289 --> 36:17.071
This is the best study
session I've ever had.

36:17.073 --> 36:19.216
They actually believed you?

36:19.218 --> 36:21.232
Why wouldn't they. I couldn't tell them
we were meeting

36:21.233 --> 36:24.719
some cute senior we met online.
They'd freak.

36:41.553 --> 36:44.495
Where is that cute guy?

36:46.001 --> 36:48.816
Speaking of freaking...

36:53.809 --> 36:55.919
Hey, girls.

36:55.921 --> 36:57.455
What are you doing here?

36:57.457 --> 36:59.663
You were supposed
to just drop us off, not follow us in.

36:59.665 --> 37:01.263
It's a mall.
Valentine's Day.

37:01.265 --> 37:02.704
I'm buying Kate a gift.

37:02.705 --> 37:04.271
Ooh, what'd you get her?

37:04.273 --> 37:06.479
Oh, uh, just gloves.

37:06.481 --> 37:09.840
In a pink bag?
Those are not gloves.

37:09.841 --> 37:12.686
So, uh, what's up
with these boys from your class?

37:12.689 --> 37:13.615
They're running late.

37:13.617 --> 37:14.959
Ahh.

37:14.961 --> 37:16.367
Ok, well,

37:16.369 --> 37:17.712
don't miss your curfew.

37:17.713 --> 37:20.175
I won't.
don't you trust me?

37:20.177 --> 37:21.968
Yeah, I trust you.
It's the boys I don't trust.

37:21.969 --> 37:24.463
Ok. Well, I'm gonna
leave you guys to it.

37:24.465 --> 37:26.543
Uh, just remember,
boys that run late

37:26.545 --> 37:28.047
are not worth waiting for.

37:28.049 --> 37:29.327
Bye.
Bye, Chris.

37:29.329 --> 37:30.575
Bye, Mr. Callahan.

37:30.577 --> 37:32.047
Bye, you guys.

37:32.049 --> 37:34.800
I can't believe it.
Your Uncle's a total stalker.

37:34.801 --> 37:36.495
Right? I don't know why
he can't just accept

37:36.497 --> 37:39.983
that I'm not a little
girl anymore. Jeez.

37:39.985 --> 37:41.167
Hey, sweetie, it's me.

37:41.169 --> 37:43.631
I, uh--look, I just want
to clear the air

37:43.633 --> 37:45.775
and let you know
that I'm really sorry.

37:45.777 --> 37:48.015
We definitely should have
discussed Meg dating

37:48.017 --> 37:50.768
before I gave the approval
for her to do that. And...

37:50.769 --> 37:53.167
But if it's any consolation,
I'm at the mall right now,

37:53.169 --> 37:56.559
and I'm planning on sticking around
to keep an eye on them.

37:56.561 --> 37:58.031
But, uh, they're doing great.

37:58.033 --> 38:01.167
Except for the fact they may have just
been stood up for the first time.

38:01.169 --> 38:02.479
But...[Laughs]

38:02.481 --> 38:04.879
I, uh, I love you,
and I do feel bad.

38:04.881 --> 38:08.656
So bad, as a matter of fact, that
I bought you something amazing.

38:08.657 --> 38:12.239
It's like, red, and it's got
black stripes,

38:12.241 --> 38:13.487
and a strap.

38:13.489 --> 38:16.239
It's gonna look
so hot on you.

38:16.241 --> 38:19.760
Uh, I'll show you
when you get home, ok?

38:26.737 --> 38:28.207
Where are they?

38:28.209 --> 38:29.871
I don't know.

38:33.777 --> 38:35.855
Sorry.

38:51.441 --> 38:53.359
Oh, they're not coming.

38:53.361 --> 38:55.087
What? Why not?

38:55.089 --> 38:58.511
I don't want
to talk about it.

